{{Wireless embedded system |brand=D-Link |model=DIR-825 |revision=D1 |upc= |ean= |asin= |price= |est_release_date= |fcc_date=08/28/2013 |manuf_country=China |manuf=Shenzhen Gongjin Electronics |manuf_model= |manuf_rev= |availability=common |type=wireless router |fcc_id=KA2IR825D1 |ic_id=4216A-IR825D1 |pwr_v=12 |pwr_amp=2 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=Realtek |cpu1_model=RTL8197D |cpu1_cspeed= |fla1=8 |fla1_brand= |fla1_model=SPI |fla1_num= |ram1=64 |ram1_brand=Nanya |ram1_model= |ram1_num= |expansion_if_types=USB 2.0 |expansion_usb_num=1 |jtag=yes,, 12-pad header,, J11 |serial=yes,, 4-pad header,, J22 |wi1_chip1_brand=Realtek |wi1_chip1_model=RTL8192DR |wi1_802dot11_protocols=an |wi1_ant_conn= |wi1_txchains=2 |wi1_rxchains=2 |wi1_sstreams=2 |wi2_chip1_brand=Realtek |wi2_chip1_model=RTL8192CE |wi2_802dot11_protocols=bgn |wi2_ant_conn= |wi2_txchains=2 |wi2_rxchains=2 |wi2_sstreams=2 |eth_none= |eth_cpu=true |sw_cpu= |sw_brand=Realtek |sw_model=RTL8367RB |lan_speed=1G |lan_ports=4 |wan_ports=1 |flags= |tp_firmware= |802dot11_protocols=abgn |default_ssid= |default_ssid_regex= |default_ip=192.168.0.1 |default_user=admin |default_pass=admin |oui= |oui_eth= }} This model is shown to sit upright (like the [[ZyXEL NBG5715]]) in the FCC docs.
"AP699GE9N3.CT165B-5-DB-DL" and "REV1.0" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. :(See also [http://www.globalsources.com/si/AS/Shenzhen-Gongjin/6008808322716/pdtl/Wireless-Router/1062107315.htm '''SGE''' AP699GE9N3.AU89-5] and FCC ID: [https://fcc.io/V4V/AP699E8N8U31H4 V4VAP699E8N8U31H4]..) The device is shown as using two '''Airgain''' antennas (likely ''N2430GND''s, :like the [[D-Link DIR-815 rev C1]]).
The FCC manual states the default SSIDs for the device are '''DIR-825''' and '''DIR-825-5G'''.. :but the accuracy of the manual is questionable.
The power supply shown in the FCC external photos is a '''Shenzhen Gongjin Electronics Co., Ltd.''' :S24B12-120A200-Y4 (100-240VAC ~ 50/60Hz, max. 0.7A -> 12VDC, 2A).
